CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, December 1, 1938, pg. 18, reads: "The Big Apple in Pittsburg, [Pittsburgh] PA. was the thing during the formal festivities of the 'Smoketowners,' a club of the super fashionable young men about the smokey city.  That 'Boggie [Boogie] Woogie' artist is Seabrone [Sebrone]  King, of Boley, Oklahoma, a Howard University student.  Edith Brown is his dancing partner."
TitMainTitle: Sebrone King dancing with Edith Brown, seen from behind, in Loendi Club
